Speaking of the evil jester, in this episode Jestro uses some newly-made monsters to attack a town far from the capitol where he thinks he's safe from the Knights' reach. We see two parallel stories here: the Knights training, learning more about digital magic and getting organized as a team and at the same time we see Jestro making monsters, trying to learn how his powers work and talking to the Book. In the end, the Knights roll up in their castle and defeat Jestro and his marauding monsters. Lance thinks he should be the leader because he's a snot. “Of course I'm the leader…I'm a Richmond.”

The Book of Monsters actually tells Jestro NOT to feed it to him he tells Jestro he's not ready for that kind of power. But Jestro doesn't listen. Now the Book unleashes chaotic monsters and Jestro uses them to attack the King and his party who are on a business-related tour of the kingdom. programme.title: I'M LIVE
programme.desc: Joining us on this week's episode of I'm LIVE is the band 87dance! 87dance is composed of vocalist and producer BETHEBLUE, guitarist Park Seong-ho, drummer Lee Jung-yeol, and bassist Choi Jun-young. This quartet made its debut in 2019 with its self-titled EP, “Palchilldance,” and quickly made itself known to the public with its unique soundscapes and fashion styles. They are now expanding their reach beyond Korea, being selected for UP NEXT KOREA by Apple Music and SPOTIFY FRESH FINDS. In this episode, 87dance performs “How can i forget you girl,” “even if fall into a fail,” “love in balcony,” “YOU'RE MY CAKE,” and more. Tune in to I'm LIVE and meet 87dance!

programme.title: I'M LIVE
programme.desc: Joining us on this week's I'm LIVE is super-talented singer and rapper Heize! Heize engraved her name in the minds of the public in 2015 through a competition program focusing on female rappers called “Unpretty Rapstar Season 2.” To no one's surprise, her song “Don't Come Back,” released right after the show, topped all the music charts and came into the spotlight for her songwriting, singing, and rapping skills and also for her emotion-tugging lyrics. This artist recently released her second full-length album, “Undo,” to showcase her growth as an artist, which has been a great success this time again. In this episode, Heize performs “You, Clouds, Rain,” “Thief,” “And July,” “HAPPEN,” “Don't Know You,” and her latest song “Undo.” Tune in to I'm LIVE and meet Heize!

programme.title: Lady Gaga
programme.desc: Lady Gaga's performance at the iTunes Festival in London on September 1, 2013 marks the superstar's first full concert since the The Born This Way Ball. It is an eight song set containing the world premiere of seven tracks from her fourth album, ARTPOP: "Aura" "MANiCURE" "Artpop" "Jewels N' Drugs" ft. T.I., Too $hort and Twista "Sexxx Dreams", "Swine" and "I Wanna Be With You", a song that transformed into "Dope" for ARTPOP. During the concert, captured stunningly in HD, Gaga says that she's "a bit like Dorothy right now." The stage is her Kansas, the crowd is her family, and their reunion is pure magic. Lady Gaga, her dancers, and her band traverse through visual and musical themes of love, sex, violence, beauty, danger, empowerment, hustle, lust, and above all ART. Throughout, Gaga lays her heart bare for the audience and the cameras with every note sung and every word spoken.

programme.desc: Being headline at one of the biggest festivals in the world is not for everyone! Coldplay, which is not any band, decided to turn the show into a historic night for those who went to Glastonbury. It all started with the fact that the show consecrated Coldplay as the first band playing FOUR times on the 'Pyramid Stage' (main stage of the festival)! With the performance ending a few hours ago, Coldplay completed six shows in the history of the big music event. Speaking of incredible numbers, the band made Xylobands available to over 100,000 people at Glastonbury!
